Project Report: Dynamic To-Do List Application

Aim: To build a persistent CRUD application using Node.js, SQLite, and Vanilla JS.

1. Database Schema (Table: tasks)

id: INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT

title: TEXT NOT NULL (Validates non-empty & max 50 chars)

description: TEXT

priority: TEXT (Low, Medium, High)

isDone: INTEGER (0 = Active, 1 = Completed)

createdAt: DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP

2. REST API Endpoints

GET /tasks: Fetch all tasks (Sorted by completion status).

POST /tasks: Create a new task with title, desc, and priority.

PUT /tasks/:id: Full update of task title and priority.

PATCH /tasks/:id/status: Toggle completion (Done/Undone).

DELETE /tasks/:id: Permanent removal from SQLite DB.

3. Challenges Faced

Real-time Sync: Implementing fetch() APIs with async/await to ensure the UI updates immediately without page reloads.

State Management: Handling filters (All/Active/Completed) while keeping the search functionality active at the same time.

UI/UX: Creating a modern "Academic Dashboard" that remains easy to read but includes advanced features like a Productivity Progress Ring.